#. Tag: title
#: manual.docbook:299
#, no-c-format
msgid "Drumkit Concept"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:301
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Let's start with a little history on the concept of Drumkits within in "
"Hydrogen. It began as a dedicated drum machine but has evolved into a "
"versatile <link linkend=\"def.sample\">sample</link>-based sound synthesizer/"
"sequencer that is capable of generating and manipulating all sorts of "
"sounds. Hence the original \"Drumkit\" terminology is slightly misleading. "
"You can load any kind of sound into a \"Drumkit\" and manipulate that sound "
"just like playing a regular synthesizer. This is also the main reason why "
"the <link linkend=\"chpt.pattern_editor.piano_mode\">Piano Roll Editor</"
"link> was introduced."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:309
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To sum it up, nowadays a Drumkit is a collection of a number of instruments "
"(snare, kick, sampled voice, bass sound ...), using one or more <link "
"linkend=\"def.component\">components</link> which each can consist of "
"multiple <link linkend=\"def.layer\">layered</link> samples."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:316
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In case you are not familiar with the world of sound synthesis, you can "
"check out the <link linkend=\"glossary\">Glossary</link> for a number of "
"useful definitions."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: manual.docbook:324
#, no-c-format
msgid "MIDI-mapping and Virtual Keyboard"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:326
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Instead of playing back programmed patterns Hydrogen can also be used "
"synthesize drum sounds for incoming <abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> or keyboard events."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:330
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using the <emphasis role=\"bold\">Input mode</emphasis> in the <link linkend="
"\"sect.main_menu.options\">Options</link> tab of the Main Menu you can "
"choose between two different ways to emulate sound. <option>Drumkit</option> "
"maps different <abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> events and keyboard inputs to different "
"instruments of the current drumkit while <option>Instrument</option> maps "
"them to pitch-shifted samples of the instrument currently selected in the "
"<link linkend=\"chpt.song_editor\">Song Editor</link>. You can think of "
"these modes as input versions of both the <link linkend=\"chpt."
"pattern_editor.drumkit\">Drumkit Editor</link> and the <link linkend=\"chpt."
"pattern_editor.piano_mode\">Piano Roll Editor</link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:334
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Which <emphasis role=\"bold\"><abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> input</emphasis> maps to "
"which instrument is depending of the <link linkend=\"chpt.instrument_editor."
"midi_out_settings\">Note</link> parameter in the Instrument Editor set for "
"in each particular drumkit. An example for the <emphasis>GMRockKit</"
"emphasis> is shown in the <link linkend=\"chpt.pattern_editor.midi_mapping"
"\">table</link> below."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:339
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In order to process incoming <abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> messages, you have to "
"enable the <emphasis role=\"bold\">Use output note as input</emphasis> "
"option and set up the overall <abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> support in the <link "
"linkend=\"chpt.preferences.midi_tab\"><abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> system</link> "
"tab of the Preferences dialog first."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:344
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Alternatively you can use the <emphasis role=\"bold\">Virtual keyboard</"
"emphasis> provided in Hydrogen. It maps a number of keys of your computer "
"keyboard to incoming note and allows you to use it as a traditional "
"<abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> keyboard. The mapping is shown in the <link linkend="
"\"chpt.pattern_editor.midi_mapping\">table</link> as well as in <link "
"linkend=\"fig.letters_keyboard\">figure</link> below."
msgstr ""

