"        <command>-s, --song &#60;File&#62;           Load a song (*.h2song) "
"at startup</command>\n"
"        <command>-k, --kit &#60;DrumkitName&#62;     Load a drumkit at "
"startup</command>\n"
"        <command>-V, --verbose &#60;Level&#62;       Level, if present, may "
"be None, Error, Warning, Info, Debug or 0xHHHH</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: manual.docbook:899
#, no-c-format
msgid "Preferences"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:901
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Via this window most of the configurations and customization can be altered. "
"The Preferences Dialog can be accessed via the <parameter>Options</"
"parameter> element in the <link linkend=\"chpt.main_menu\">Main Menu</link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:904
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"All changes done in the Preferences Dialog - if not noted otherwise via a "
"popup - will take effect when clicking the <emphasis role=\"bold\">Ok</"
"emphasis> button at the bottom of the window."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: manual.docbook:910 manual.docbook:2972 manual.docbook:3632
#, no-c-format
msgid "General"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: manual.docbook:913
#, no-c-format
msgid "The General Tab"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:923
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Language</emphasis>: chooses one of the translations "
"Hydrogen is available in."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:927 manual.docbook:1039
#, no-c-format
msgid "For this setting to take effect you have to restart Hydrogen."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:933
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If your mother tongue is not available or the corresponding translation is "
"flawed or incomplete, you would have an accessible way to contribute to "
"Hydrogen at hand. Please see the <link linkend=\"sect.main_menu.info"
"\">About</link> dialog in the Info option of the Main menu for information "
"of how to contact the Hydrogen dev team."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:942
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Reopen last used song</emphasis>: determines whether "
"Hydrogen will open the last used song during startup or an empty song "
"instead."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:948
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Reopen last used playlist</emphasis>: determines "
"whether the last used <link linkend=\"chpt.playlist_editor\">Playlist</link> "
"will be loaded during startup or none at all."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:952
#, no-c-format
msgid "This can come in handy when you are using Hydrogen live."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:959
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Use relative paths for playlist</emphasis>: "
"specifies whether the path names in the stored <link linkend=\"chpt."
"file_types.h2playlist\">.h2playlist</link> file will contain absolute paths "
"or a path relative to the <filename role=\"directory\">playlist</filename> "
"folder in the Hydrogen data directory (usually <filename role=\"directory\">"
"$HOME/.hydrogen/data/</filename>)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:965
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using relative paths might be handy when using your playlist on different "
"computers or user profiles."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:972
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Hide keyboard input cursor</emphasis>: hides the "
"keyboard cursor until you press a key on you keyboard (see <xref linkend="
"\"chpt.keyboard_and_mouse\"/>). By enabling this feature you can switch to "
"the look and feel of the interaction with the <link linkend=\"chpt."
"pattern_editor\">Pattern Editor</link> and <link linkend=\"chpt.song_editor"
"\">Song Editor</link> prior to Hydrogen v1.1."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:978
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Use LASH</emphasis>: enables <abbrev>LASH</abbrev> "
"(<abbrev>LASH</abbrev> Audio Session Handler) support within Hydrogen. This "
"allows you to recover a particular song associated with a session."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:983
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You may consider using the more advanced <link linkend=\"chpt.overview."
"session_management.nsm\">NSM</link> support of Hydrogen which gives you many "
"additional features, like restoring all <abbrev>JACK</abbrev> connections or "
"creating a per-session configuration."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:990
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Beat counter drift compensation in 1/10 ms</"
"emphasis>: allows you to compensate for system latency. The provided number "
"will be added to each consecutive triggering of the <link linkend=\"sect."
"main_toolbar.tap_tempo_beat_counter.beat_counter\">Beat Counter</link>. The "
"allowed range is from <option>-200</option> to <option>200</option>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:995
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is quite handy if you are using different sound cards or external "
"<abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> devices, like a keyboard or an e-drum, with "
"mismatching clocks."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:998
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In order to find useful values for these, you will need to take some time to "
"play with it. Also, you may want different values depending on the speed of "
"your hardware, audio devices, drivers, etc. Using the Beat Counter "
"effectively requires practice."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1009
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Beat counter start offset in ms</emphasis>: sets the "
"time between the Beat Counter's last input stroke and when the song starts "
"playing. Its allowed range is from <option>-500</option> to <option>500</"
"option>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1015
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Beat Counter has to be set to <emphasis role=\"bold\">Set <abbrev>BPM</"
"abbrev> and play</emphasis> - <inlinemediaobject> <imageobject> <imagedata "
"fileref=\"img/btn_set_play_on.png\" format=\"PNG\"/> </imageobject> </"
"inlinemediaobject> should be displayed in the bottom right corner - for this "
"setting to take effect."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1029
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Maximum number of bars</emphasis>: sets the maximum "
"number of supported bars/patterns for a single song. Its allowed range is "
"from <option>1</option> to <option>800</option>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1035
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Maximum number of layers</emphasis>: sets the "
"maximum number of <link linkend=\"def.layer\">layers</link> for a single "
"instrument. Its allowed range is from <option>16</option> to <option>8192</"
"option>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1047
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Path to the Rubberband command-line utility</"
"emphasis>: sets the absolute path to the <command>rubberband</command> "
"command line interface (CLI) Hydrogen will use for stretching samples in the "
"<link linkend=\"chpt.sample_editor.pitch\">Sample Editor</link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1051
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This option is only available if your version of Hydrogen does "
"<emphasis>not</emphasis> already has Rubber Band support compiled into it. "
"If it does and the option is hot shown, everything is already configured and "
"you don't have to worry about Rubber Band at all."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1057
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you are using Ubuntu, you can install Rubber Band from the Software "
"Center via the package <option>rubberband-cli</option>. For other Linux "
"distros please check your package manager and for other platforms please "
"check <ulink url=\"http://breakfastquay.com/rubberband/\">the Rubber Band "
"site </ulink>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1066
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If Rubber Band is installed and configured correctly, you will see an extra "
"button <inlinemediaobject> <imageobject> <imagedata fileref=\"img/rubber_off."
"png\" format=\"PNG\"/> </imageobject> </inlinemediaobject> button in the "
"<link linkend=\"sect.main_toolbar.bpm_control_and_metronome\">Main Toolbar</"
"link>. You can use this behavior to verify your configuration."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: manual.docbook:1084
#, no-c-format
msgid "Audio System"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: manual.docbook:1087
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Audio System Tab"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1097
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Audio System</emphasis>: let's you choose the audio "
"driver used by Hydrogen to connect to your computer's sound card."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1101
#, no-c-format
msgid "Available options:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1107
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<option>Auto</option>: Hydrogen will try a number of different drivers in a "
"predetermined order, choose the first working one, and display the result."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1112
#, no-c-format
msgid "This option is recommended for beginners."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1121
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<option>JACK</option>: The <abbrev>JACK</abbrev> driver is a professional "
"audio server which permits very low lag and exchanges with other audio "
"software. The <abbrev>JACK</abbrev> server will start automatically if not "
"already running."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1128
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"We strongly recommend using this driver to have the best out of Hydrogen."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1135
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>ALSA</option>: The widely adopted Linux standard audio driver."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1140
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<option>OSS</option>: The <abbrev>OSS</abbrev> audio driver uses <filename>/"
"dev/dsp</filename> and it's based on the <abbrev>OSS</abbrev> interface "
"which is supported by the vast majority of sound cards available for Linux; "
"this said, the use of this audio driver blocks <filename>/dev/dsp</filename> "
"until Hydrogen is closed i.e. unusable by any other software. Use it as last "
"resort."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1150
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>PortAudio</option>: An open-source multi platform audio driver."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1155
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>CoreAudio</option>: A driver for MacOS."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1159
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<option>PulseAudio</option>: A driver for the cross platform PulseAudio "
"sound server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1167
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Device</emphasis>: specifies the particular sound "
"card the audio driver will use."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1173
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Buffer size</emphasis>: specifies the size of the "
"batch of time Hydrogen will process in one run. Supported values are from "
"<option>100</option> to <option>5000</option>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1179
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Sample rate</emphasis>: specifies the number of data "
"points the audio signal will contain within one second."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1183
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you are using the <abbrev>JACK</abbrev> audio driver, the sample rate can "
"not be altered from within Hydrogen and the audio driver configuration "
"should happen before starting the <abbrev>JACK</abbrev> server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1192
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Track output</emphasis>: determines which audio "
"settings will be applied to the outgoing audio of the per-instrument "
"<abbrev>JACK</abbrev> output ports."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1195
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>Post-Fader</option>:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1197
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"note <link linkend=\"chpt.pattern_editor.note_properties.velocity"
"\">velocity</link> and <link linkend=\"chpt.pattern_editor.note_properties."
"pan\">pan</link>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: link
#: manual.docbook:1198 manual.docbook:1205
#, no-c-format
msgid "layer gain"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1199
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"component <link linkend=\"chpt.instrument_editor.layers.controls."
"component_volume\">gain</link> and <link linkend=\"chpt.mixer."
"component_strips.fader_and_lcd\">volume</link>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1200
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"instrument <link linkend=\"chpt.instrument_editor.gain_and_mute_group"
"\">gain</link>, <link linkend=\"chpt.mixer.channel_strips.pan\">pan</link>, "
"and <link linkend=\"chpt.mixer.channel_strips.fader_and_lcd\">volume</link>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1202
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>Pre-Fader</option>:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1204
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"note <link linkend=\"chpt.pattern_editor.note_properties.velocity"
"\">velocity</link>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1209
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This option is only available if the <abbrev>JACK</abbrev> audio driver was "
"selected and it will only take effect if the <emphasis role=\"bold\">Connect "
"to default <abbrev>JACK</abbrev> output ports</emphasis> option is checked."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1215
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">BBT sync method</emphasis>: if Hydrogen uses "
"<abbrev>JACK</abbrev> transport in the presence of an external <abbrev>JACK</"
"abbrev> Timebase master (TBM), it will use the provided measure and tempo "
"information instead of the local one of either the <link linkend=\"sect."
"main_toolbar.bpm_control_and_metronome\">song's tempo</link> or the Tempo "
"Markers added to the <link linkend=\"chpt.song_editor.timeline\">Timeline</"
"link>. But due to limitations in the current implementation, Hydrogen can "
"not set both measure and speed provided by <abbrev>JACK</abbrev> for "
"arbitrary pattern combinations. You have two options here. Either drop all "
"measure changes in the TBM and work with tempo changes only to support "
"arbitrary patterns (using option <option>constant measure</option>) or to "
"keep the length of each pattern consistent with the corresponding measure in "
"the TBM and to use both tempo and measure provided by <abbrev>JACK</abbrev> "
"(option <option>matching bars</option>)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1232 manual.docbook:1267 manual.docbook:1288
#: manual.docbook:1311
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This option is only available if the <abbrev>JACK</abbrev> audio driver was "
"selected."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1235
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For this option to take effect the <inlinemediaobject> <imageobject> "
"<imagedata fileref=\"img/btn_jack_transport_off.png\" format=\"PNG\"/> </"
"imageobject> </inlinemediaobject> button has to be activated and the "
"<inlinemediaobject> <imageobject> <imagedata fileref=\"img/"
"btn_jack_master_off.png\" format=\"PNG\"/> </imageobject> </"
"inlinemediaobject> button deactivated in the <link linkend=\"sect."
"main_toolbar.jack_control\">Main Toolbar</link> (next to having a "
"<abbrev>JACK</abbrev> TBM application)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1253
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Hydrogen can be registered as <abbrev>JACK</abbrev> Timebase Master via the "
"<link linkend=\"sect.main_toolbar.jack_control\">Main Toolbar</link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1259
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Connect to default <abbrev>JACK</abbrev> output "
"ports</emphasis>: connects the main stereo <abbrev>JACK</abbrev> output "
"ports of the <link linkend=\"chpt.mixer.master_fader_strip\">Master Fader "
"Strip</link> to the default <abbrev>JACK</abbrev> input ports of your system "
"(<emphasis>system:playback_1</emphasis> and <emphasis>system:playback_2</"
"emphasis>). This will be done every time Hydrogen starts up or the "
"<abbrev>JACK</abbrev> audio driver is restarted."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1274
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Create per-instrument <abbrev>JACK</abbrev> output "
"ports</emphasis>: in addition to the main stereo output Hydrogen will "
"register <abbrev>JACK</abbrev> output ports for every single instrument."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1281
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This can be useful if you want to add effects to a single instrument with "
"jack-rack for example."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1294
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are no <abbrev>JACK</abbrev> output ports for the <link linkend=\"sect."
"main_toolbar.bpm_control_and_metronome\">Metronome</link> and the <link "
"linkend=\"chpt.song_editor.playbackTrack\">Playback Track</link>. Their "
"audio is only available via the main stereo output ports of Hydrogen."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1300
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Enable <abbrev>JACK</abbrev> timebase master "
"support</emphasis>: whether Hydrogen will respond to or ignore the incoming "
"BBT (tempo and measure) information sent by the <abbrev>JACK</abbrev> server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1305
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Some <abbrev>JACK</abbrev> clients are not well written or have fallen into "
"despair. As a result Hydrogen could receive nuisance signals messing up its "
"playback. If you encounter weird jumps in the transport position and/or "
"Hydrogen is out of sync after relocating the transport position, you might "
"try to uncheck this option."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1318
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Apply and restart output</emphasis>: restarts the "
"audio driver and makes all settings specified above take effect without "
"closing and reopening the entire Preferences dialog."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1324
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Polyphony</emphasis>: specifies the maximum number "
"of notes played simultaneously. Supported values are from <option>1</option> "
"to <option>512</option>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1328
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Depending on your CPU Hydrogen might be overrunning your audio driver due to "
"this parameter."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1335
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Metronome volume</emphasis>: sets the volume of the "
"<link linkend=\"sect.main_toolbar.bpm_control_and_metronome\">Metronome</"
"link>. Supported values are from <option>1</option> to <option>100</option>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1341
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Interpolate resampling</emphasis>: specifies the "
"type of resampling applied if a <link linkend=\"def.sample\">sample</link> "
"does not use the same Sample Rate as Hydrogen."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: manual.docbook:1351
#, no-c-format
msgid "MIDI System"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: manual.docbook:1354
#, no-c-format
msgid "The MIDI System Tab"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1364
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\"><abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> driver</emphasis>: selects the "
"<abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> driver Hydrogen will use to send <abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> "
"messages."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1370
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Input</emphasis>: selects the device Hydrogen will "
"expect <abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> messages to receive from."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1376
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Output</emphasis>: selects the device Hydrogen will "
"send <abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> messages to."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1382
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Channel</emphasis>: specifies whether Hydrogen "
"should listen to <abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> messages on one particular of the 16 "
"available channels or on all of them."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1388
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Ignore note-off</emphasis>: specifies whether "
"Hydrogen will respond to the <emphasis>note-off</emphasis> <abbrev>MIDI</"
"abbrev> message."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1392
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This makes better use of the drumkit samples used in Hydrogen when working "
"with certain external <abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> devices. But it may also discard "
"<emphasis>Cymbal choke</emphasis> messages in some e-drums."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1399
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Enable <abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> feedback</emphasis>: "
"specifies whether Hydrogen will send a message about updated values every "
"time a certain parameter is changed. These parameters are"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1404
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"the <link linkend=\"chpt.mixer.master_fader_strip\">Master Fader Strip</"
"link> volume and mute state"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1409
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"an Instrument Strip <link linkend=\"chpt.mixer.channel_strips.pan\">pan</"
"link>, <link linkend=\"chpt.mixer.channel_strips.fader_and_lcd\">volume</"
"link>, <link linkend=\"chpt.mixer.channel_strips.mute\">mute</link> and "
"<link linkend=\"chpt.mixer.channel_strips.solo\">solo</link> state"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1414
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"whether the <link linkend=\"sect.main_toolbar.bpm_control_and_metronome"
"\">Metronome</link> is activated"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1422
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Discard <abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> messages after action "
"has been triggered</emphasis>: specifies whether a <abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> "
"note - after performing the <abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> action associated with it "
"- should be played back or be discard."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1428
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Use output note as input note</emphasis>: specifies "
"whether the output <abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> note of an instrument specified in "
"the <link linkend=\"chpt.instrument_editor.midi_out_settings\"><abbrev>MIDI</"
"abbrev> Out Settings</link> of the Instrument Editor should be used to map "
"the input as well."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1433
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this option is unchecked, only the currently selected instrument will "
"used to play back the received <abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> notes."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1441
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using the table in the lower part of the tab you can associate <link linkend="
"\"chpt.midi.actions\"><abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> actions</link> provided by "
"Hydrogen with incoming <abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> messages. How this is done will "
"be explained in the <xref linkend=\"chpt.midi.actions\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: manual.docbook:1448
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>OSC</title>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: manual.docbook:1451
#, no-c-format
msgid "The OSC Tab"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1459
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <abbrev>OSC</abbrev> tab (<xref linkend=\"fig.preferences.osc_tab\"/>) "
"let's you modify all options associated with <abbrev>OSC</abbrev> (Open "
"Sound Control) (see chapter <link linkend=\"chpt.osc\">OSC API</link> for "
"details)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1464
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In order to see and access the <emphasis role=\"bold\">Enable OSC feedback</"
"emphasis> and <emphasis role=\"bold\">Import port</emphasis> option, "
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Enable OSC support</emphasis> has to be checked "
"first."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:1471
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Enable OSC support</emphasis>: Allows Hydrogen to "
