#. Tag: title
#: manual.docbook:4810
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mixer Settings"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:4812
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the upper right corner of Master Fader Strip there is a small \"cog\" "
"icon button:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:4821
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Click it to open the Mixer Settings window: <informalfigure id="
"\"mixerSettingsDialog\"> <mediaobject> <imageobject> <imagedata fileref="
"\"generated_en/mixerSettingsDialog.png\" format=\"PNG\"/> </imageobject> </"
"mediaobject> </informalfigure> Here you can select the <emphasis role=\"bold"
"\">Pan Law</emphasis> used by Hydrogen Mixer."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:4834
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Pan Law is the relationship between the <link linkend=\"def.pan"
"\">Resultant Pan</link> and the separate <link linkend=\"def.gain\">gains</"
"link> of left and right audio outputs. The aim is to control the horizontal "
"angle the sound seems to arrive from."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:4838
#, no-c-format
msgid "Hydrogen features one the most customizable and accurate Pan Law set."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:4841
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You will find four categories: <option>linear</option>, <option>polar</"
"option>, <option>ratio</option>, <option>quadratic</option>. Every category "
"gives a different \"scale\" or \"sensibility\" to the pan knob: the same "
"knob position will make the sound appear more lateral or central depending "
"on the category, from the most lateral (<emphasis>linear</emphasis>) to the "
"most central (<emphasis>quadratic</emphasis>)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:4849
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Then for each category you will find four options, that define a "
"<emphasis>constraint</emphasis> between the gains of the two channels:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:4854
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Balance Law (0dB)</emphasis>: when you turn the pan "
"knob from center to right, the right gain stays constant at maximum level "
"while the left gain decreases from the maximum level to 0 (and symmetrically "
"turning from center to left)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:4857
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is ideal for balancing a DUAL-channel track. It has ZERO center "
"compensation: the sound will be <emphasis>louder</emphasis> when the pan "
"knob is at <emphasis>center</emphasis> - unless channels are out of phase - "
"so you may have to readjust the volume manually with the mixer fader."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:4865
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Constant Power (-3dB)</emphasis>: the total "
"<emphasis>power</emphasis> (which is proportional to the <emphasis>square</"
"emphasis> of the gain) is constant for any position of the pan knob."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:4868
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Compared to the Balance Law, each channel gain is divided by the square root "
"of 2 when the pan knob is at center (-3.0103 dB center compensation). In a "
"common room, this constraint <emphasis>may</emphasis> give the general "
"perception of uniform volume for any pan knob position (panning a MONO "
"track)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:4876
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Constant Sum (-6dB)</emphasis>: the sum of left and "
"right gains is constant for any position of the pan knob."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:4878
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This constraint preserves the mix volumes in mono export. Compared to the "
"Balance Law, each channel gain is halved (-6.0206 dB) when the pan knob is "
"at center. If you are in an ideal anechoic room (where there are no acoustic "
"reflections) and you seat perfectly at the same distance from the speakers, "
"with this constraint the volume will be really constant for any pan "
"position, because of the linear <emphasis>super-position</emphasis> of sound "
"waves (panning a MONO track)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:4889
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Constant k-Norm (Custom dB center compensation)</"
"emphasis>: you can experiment adjusting the center compensation to your "
"taste!"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:4893
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Some hi-end studio mixers - to be used in well tuned rooms - have center "
"compensation between -3dB and -6dB."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:4901
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The four constraints should not change the perception of the "
"<emphasis>stereo angle</emphasis>, but the <emphasis>volume</emphasis> only "
"(depending on the pan knob)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:4904
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Pan Law is something you should choose <emphasis>before</emphasis> "
"starting the mix and keep untouched. Hydrogen sets the <emphasis>ratio "
"Balance Law</emphasis> by default because it was the only available law "
"until version 1.0 (so old songs and drumkits will sound the same). The "
"setting is saved in the song file but not in preferences, so it is NOT "
"remembered when you create a new song."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:4912
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Unlike in advanced mixers, Hydrogen panning makes no distinction if a track "
"is mono or dual-channel (stereo). You cannot pan each channel of stereo "
"tracks separately, nor use a balance law for them and another pan law for "
"mono tracks. If the drumkit you are using is made of true stereo samples, "
"you don't want a negative center compensation probably, so you should select "
"a Balance Law."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: manual.docbook:4926
#, no-c-format
msgid "Director"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:4938
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Director provides a quick overview of what Hydrogen is currently doing. "
"It can be opened by pressing <keycap>Alt</keycap> + <keycap>D</keycap> or by "
"via the <link linkend=\"sect.main_menu.view\">View</link> option in the Main "
"Menu."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:4942
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Director shows you the song name, a visualization of the <link linkend="
"\"sect.main_toolbar.bpm_control_and_metronome\">Metronome</link>, and the "
"<link linkend=\"chpt.song_editor.tag\">Tags</link>. Just below the metronome "
"you can see the latest tag, and below that the next upcoming tag. This way "
"you have a nice overview of what is going on, and what is about to happen in "
"the song."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:4950
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This comes in very handy when you are <link linkend=\"chpt.overview.recording"
"\">recording</link> a song, or if you are using Hydrogen live on stage."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: manual.docbook:4959
#, no-c-format
msgid "Playlist Editor"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: manual.docbook:4965
#, no-c-format
msgid "Main Window"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: manual.docbook:4968
#, no-c-format
msgid "Song List"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:4970
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Playlist Editor allows you to group various songs into a playlist and is "
"intended to ease using Hydrogen live on stage. You can access this window "
"via the <link linkend=\"sect.main_menu.view\">View</link> option of the Main "
"Menu."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:4975
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using the <link linkend=\"chpt.playlist_editor.menu\">menu</link> you can "
"add various songs to the playlist and you can arrange their order using the "
"arrow buttons to the right of the widget."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:4980
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When playback reaches the end of one song the next one won't be "
"automatically selected and played! You can select an arbitrary song in the "
"playlist using double <emphasis>left-clicking</emphasis>, by pressing the "
"hotkeys <link linkend=\"chap.shortcuts.f5\"><keycap>F5</keycap></link> and "
"<link linkend=\"chap.shortcuts.f6\"><keycap>F6</keycap></link>, or the "
"corresponding <link linkend=\"chpt.osc.command.playlist_song\">OSC</link> "
"commands."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:4983
#, no-c-format
msgid "Also note that selecting a song won't start playback automatically."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:4997
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"At the bottom of the widget you find a couple of <emphasis role=\"bold"
"\">buttons</emphasis> you already know from the <link linkend=\"sect."
"main_toolbar.transport_control\">Transport Control</link> in the Main "
"Toolbar. They do have the same purposes of starting, pausing, and stopping "
"the playback as well as moving the transport position backwards or forwards "
"by one pattern."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5002
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"While focusing the Playlist Editor instead of the main UI the usual <link "
"linkend=\"chap.shortcuts\">shortcuts</link> of Hydrogen, like <link linkend="
"\"chap.shortcuts.space\"><keycap>Space</keycap></link> for starting/pausing "
"playback, won't work."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: manual.docbook:5010 manual.docbook:5092
#, no-c-format
msgid "Scripts"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5012
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In addition, the Playlist Editor allows you to add <emphasis role=\"bold"
"\">scripts</emphasis> executed right <emphasis>before</emphasis> the "
"selected song is loaded. <note> <para> This means that e.g. <link linkend="
"\"chpt.osc.commands.all_messages\">OSC</link> commands can not be used to "
"change the state of Hydrogen as the subsequent loading of the associated "
"song would reset it immediately. </para> </note> The scripts supported in "
"the Playlist Editor are <abbrev>BASH</abbrev> scripts and one has to both "
"add a script to a song as well as to check the corresponding box in the "
"<emphasis>exec Script</emphasis> column in order to have it by your computer "
"whenever you switch to the particular song."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5026
#, no-c-format
msgid "Scripts are not supported in the Windows version of Hydrogen."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: manual.docbook:5034
#, no-c-format
msgid "Menu"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: manual.docbook:5037
#, no-c-format
msgid "Playlist"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5041
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Add song to Playlist</emphasis>: let's you select a "
"song to be added to the current playlist."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5047
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Add current song to Playlist</emphasis>: adds the "
"currently loaded song to the current playlist."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5053
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Remove selected song from Playlist</emphasis>: "
"deletes the selected song from the current playlist."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5059
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">New Playlist</emphasis>: creates a new and empty "
"playlist."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5065
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Open Playlist</emphasis>: opens an existing playlist "
"(file of type <link linkend=\"chpt.file_types.h2playlist\">.h2playlist</"
"link>)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5070
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the <link linkend=\"fig.preferences.general_tab\">General</link> tab of "
"the Preferences dialog you can configure Hydrogen to reload the last used "
"playlist."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5077
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Save Playlist</emphasis>: saves all changes done to "
"the current playlist."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5083
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Save Playlist as</emphasis>: saves the current "
"playlist into a file (of type <link linkend=\"chpt.file_types.h2playlist\">."
"h2playlist</link>) and location of your choice."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5096
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Add Script to selected song</emphasis>: associates a "
"<abbrev>BASH</abbrev> script (file of type <command>.sh</command>) to the "
"currently selected song of the playlist."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5102
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Edit selected Script</emphasis>: opens the selected "
"script with your default editor (in an external window)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5106
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When using the function for the first time Hydrogen will ask you which "
"program to use as your default editor."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5113
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Remove selected Script</emphasis>: removes the "
"selected script from the playlist."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5119
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Create a new Script</emphasis>: creates a new and "
"empty <command>.sh</command> scrip at a location of your choice."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5124
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The default one is the <filename role=\"directory\">scripts</filename> "
"folder in the Hydrogen data directory (usually <filename role=\"directory\">"
"$HOME/.hydrogen/data/</filename>)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: manual.docbook:5137
#, no-c-format
msgid "MIDI API"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5139
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In this section you can find more info about how to make Hydrogen respond to "
"<abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> messages. This is either done using the <link linkend="
"\"chpt.midi.actions\">available <abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> Actions</link> or "
"using the <link linkend=\"chpt.midi.learnable\"><abbrev>MIDI</abbrev>-"
"learnable Widgets</link>, like knobs or faders, both triggered using <link "
"linkend=\"chpt.midi.actions\"><abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> Events</link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5143
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Before you can work with <abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> actions you should have your "
"<abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> devices, drivers, and connections configured correctly "
"in the <link linkend=\"chpt.preferences.midi_tab\">MIDI System </link> tab "
"of the Preferences."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5148
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Please note that this chapter will only cover the table linking external "
"<abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> Events to Hydrogen's <abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> Actions. "
"For all other parameters of the <abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> API please see the "
"<link linkend=\"chpt.preferences.midi_tab\">MIDI System </link> tab of the "
"Preferences."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: manual.docbook:5154
#, no-c-format
msgid "MIDI Actions"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5164
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"An <abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> <emphasis role=\"bold\">Event</emphasis> is an "
"incoming <abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> message, originating from e.g. a "
"<abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> controller or an external sequencer. A <abbrev>MIDI</"
"abbrev> <emphasis role=\"bold\">Action</emphasis> is a function built into "
"Hydrogen that can be used to react to a specific <abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> "
"Event. Binding an Event to an Action can be done using the <link linkend="
"\"chpt.preferences.midi_tab\">MIDI System</link> tab of the Preferences."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5167
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can also define <abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> bindings by simply pressing the "
"<inlinemediaobject> <imageobject> <imagedata fileref=\"img/rec.png\" format="
"\"PNG\"/> </imageobject> </inlinemediaobject> button left of the Event-"
"Action binding line. A popup will inform you that Hydrogen is waiting for "
"your input. Press/hit/turn the key/pad/knob on your <abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> "
"keyboard (or controller) that you want to link to this action. The popup "
"will close and the <emphasis role=\"bold\">Event Param.</emphasis> value "
"will now show the <abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> note value of the key you pressed. "
"Once this is done you can select an Action from the action drop-down list."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5183
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can also define a binding without the <inlinemediaobject> <imageobject> "
"<imagedata fileref=\"img/rec.png\" format=\"PNG\"/> </imageobject> </"
"inlinemediaobject> button by setting the <emphasis role=\"bold\">Event Param."
"</emphasis> manually to the desired <abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> note."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5193
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <emphasis role=\"bold\">Action Param.</emphasis> column to the right of "
"the table specifies the input parameter to the Action (see the corresponding "
"<link linkend=\"chpt.midi.actions.actions\">Actions reference</link> for "
"details)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: manual.docbook:5198
#, no-c-format
msgid "Events"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5200
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Three types of <abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> Events are available (as described in "
"the <abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> standard):"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5206
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">NOTE</emphasis>: an input coming from a regular "
"black/white key of a keyboard or a drumpad."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5210
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">CC</emphasis>: controller commands coming from "
"faders or rotary controllers."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5214
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">MMC_x</emphasis>: <ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia."
"org/wiki/MIDI_Machine_Control\"> machine control events</ulink> coming from "
"buttons, like 'play' or 'stop', on a controller."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: manual.docbook:5224
#, no-c-format
msgid "Actions"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5227
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Some of the <abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> Actions require that the <emphasis role="
"\"bold\">Action Param.</emphasis> is configured. This parameter usually "
"references a specific channel, instrument, FXsend... Keep in mind that its "
"value is <emphasis>zero-based</emphasis>. So, if you want to reference "
"channel 1 you have to enter <option>0</option> in the <emphasis role=\"bold"
"\">Action Param.</emphasis> field (<option>1</option> for channel 2, "
"<option>2</option> for channel 3, and so on)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5236
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">&#60;&#60;_PREVIOUS_BAR</emphasis>: moves the "
"playhead to the previous pattern/bar."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5243
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">&#62;&#62;_NEXT_BAR</emphasis>: moves the playhead "
"to the next pattern/bar."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5249
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">BEATCOUNTER</emphasis>: calculates the average time "
"passing between successive encounters of this commands and uses it to set "
"the current tempo using the <link linkend=\"sect.main_toolbar."
"tap_tempo_beat_counter.beat_counter\">Beat Counter</link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5256
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">BPM_CC_RELATIVE</emphasis>: changes the tempo "
"relative to the current tempo, using a controller. Using the <emphasis role="
"\"bold\">Action Param</emphasis> you can specify by how much the current "
"tempo will change. If the incoming Event is <option>-1</option> (negative), "
"the tempo will be increased and if it's <option>1</option> (positive), it "
"will be increased."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5259
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This Action will have no effect if Hydrogen is both in <link linkend=\"chpt."
"song_editor.editor_modes.song_mode\">Song mode</link> and the <link linkend="
"\"chpt.song_editor.timeline\">Timeline</link> is activated."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5268
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">BPM_DECR</emphasis>: decreases the current tempo by "
"the supplied value."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5273 manual.docbook:5285 manual.docbook:5298
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This Action will have no effect if Hydrogen is in <link linkend=\"chpt."
"song_editor.editor_modes.song_mode\">Song mode</link> or <link linkend="
"\"chpt.song_editor.timeline\">Timeline</link> is activated."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5281
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">BPM_FINE_CC_RELATIVE</emphasis>: as <xref linkend="
"\"chpt.midi.actions.actions.bpm_cc_relative\"/> but with changes 100 times "
"smaller than the value specified in <emphasis role=\"bold\">Action Param</"
"emphasis>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5293
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">BPM_INCR</emphasis>: increases the current tempo by "
"the supplied value."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5305
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">EFFECTx_LEVEL_ABSOLUTE</emphasis>: changes the <link "
"linkend=\"chpt.mixer.channel_strips.fx_volume\">volume level of an FX</link> "
"<option>x</option> provided as an integer between <option>0</option> and "
"<option>127</option>. The value you enter in the <emphasis role=\"bold"
"\">Action Param</emphasis> determines the <link linkend=\"chpt.mixer."
"channel_strips\">Instrument Channel Strip</link> the Action will be applied "
"to."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5310
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis role=\"bold\">EFFECTx_LEVEL_RELATIVE</emphasis>:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5313
#, no-c-format
msgid "Not implemented yet."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5320
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">FILTER_CUTOFF_LEVEL_ABSOLUTE</emphasis>: for a value "
"of <option>0</option> it sets the <link linkend=\"chpt.instrument_editor."
"filter\">Filter Cutoff</link> of the instrument strip specified using the "
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Action Param</emphasis> to <option>0</option>. For "
"all other values it sets the cutoff to the provided number divided by 127.0."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5329
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">MASTER_VOLUME_ABSOLUTE</emphasis>: sets the <link "
"linkend=\"chpt.mixer.master_fader_strip\">Master output volume</link> to the "
"value provided by the <abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> event times 1.5 and divided by "
"127."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5333
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">MASTER_VOLUME_RELATIVE</emphasis>: changes the <link "
"linkend=\"chpt.mixer.master_fader_strip\">Master output volume</link>, "
"relative to its current setting. For a value of <option>0</option> it sets "
"the volume of the master fader to 0. For a value of <option>1</option> it "
"increases its volume by 0.05 and for all other values it decreases it by "
"0.05. (<option>-1</option>: -0.05 , <option>0</option>: 0 ,<option>1</"
"option>: +0.05)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5341
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">MUTE</emphasis>: <link linkend=\"def.mute\">mutes</"
"link> the <link linkend=\"chpt.mixer.master_fader_strip\">Master output</"
"link> (sequencer keeps running)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5345
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">MUTE_TOGGLE</emphasis>: toggles the <link linkend="
"\"def.mute\">muting</link> of the <link linkend=\"chpt.mixer."
"master_fader_strip\">Master output</link> (sequencer keeps running)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5350
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">PAN_ABSOLUTE</emphasis>: changes the <link linkend="
"\"def.pan\">pan</link> of an <link linkend=\"chpt.mixer.channel_strips.pan"
"\">instrument</link> determined by the <emphasis role=\"bold\">Action Param</"
"emphasis> to the absolute value - from <option>0</option> to <option>127</"
"option> - that the linked controller sends to Hydrogen."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5354
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">PAN_RELATIVE</emphasis>: changes the <link linkend="
"\"def.pan\">pan</link> of an <link linkend=\"chpt.mixer.channel_strips.pan"
"\">instrument</link> determined by the <emphasis role=\"bold\">Action Param</"
"emphasis> relative to the current value. For a value of <option>1</option> "
"it increase the pan by 0.05. For all other values it decreases it by 0.05. "
"(<option>-1</option>: -0.05 , <option>1</option>: +0.05)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5360
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis role=\"bold\">PAUSE</emphasis>: pauses playback."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5364
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis role=\"bold\">PLAY</emphasis>: starts playback."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5368
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">PLAY/PAUSE_TOGGLE</emphasis>: works the same as "
"<xref linkend=\"chpt.midi.actions.actions.play\"/> if the playback has not "
"started yet and same as. <xref linkend=\"chpt.midi.actions.actions.pause\"/> "
"otherwise. (The playhead will not return to the start of the song, but will "
"stay at its current position)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5376
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">PLAY/STOP_TOGGLE</emphasis>: works the same as <xref "
"linkend=\"chpt.midi.actions.actions.play\"/> if the playback has not started "
"yet and same as. <xref linkend=\"chpt.midi.actions.actions.stop\"/> "
"otherwise."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5383
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">PLAYLIST_NEXT_SONG</emphasis>: opens the song in the "
"current <link linkend=\"chpt.playlist_editor\">playlist</link> corresponding "
"to the song number specified in <emphasis role=\"bold\">Action Param</"
"emphasis>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5390
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">PLAYLIST_PREV_SONG</emphasis>: opens the previous "
"song in the current <link linkend=\"chpt.playlist_editor\">playlist</link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5397
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">PLAYLIST_SONG</emphasis>: opens the next song in the "
"current <link linkend=\"chpt.playlist_editor\">playlist</link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5404
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">RECORD/STROBE_TOGGLE</emphasis>: toggles <link "
"linkend=\"chpt.overview.recording\">recording</link> (same as pressing the "
"<link linkend=\"sect.main_toolbar.transport_control\">record button</link> "
"in the main toolbar)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5412
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">RECORD_EXIT</emphasis>: deactivates <link linkend="
"\"chpt.overview.recording\">recording</link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5419
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">RECORD_READY</emphasis>: toggles <link linkend="
"\"chpt.overview.recording\">recording</link> (same as pressing the <link "
"linkend=\"sect.main_toolbar.transport_control\">record button</link> in the "
"main toolbar) if the playback has not started yet."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5427
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">RECORD_STROBE</emphasis>: activates <link linkend="
"\"chpt.overview.recording\">recording</link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5434
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">REDO_ACTION</emphasis>: redoes the previous undone "
"action."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5440
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">SELECT_AND_PLAY_PATTERN</emphasis>: works as <xref "
"linkend=\"chpt.midi.actions.actions.select_next_pattern\"/> combined with "
"<xref linkend=\"chpt.midi.actions.actions.play\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5447
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">SELECT_INSTRUMENT</emphasis>: selects the instrument "
"in the drumkit corresponding to the number supplied in the incoming "
"<abbrev>MIDI</abbrev> Event."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5452
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">SELECT_NEXT_PATTERN</emphasis>: switches to the "
"pattern specified in <emphasis role=\"bold\">Action Param</emphasis>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: manual.docbook:5457
#, no-c-format
